Collections are arranged into groups for searching. Click on a group name to search the collections in that group. A collection may include some content outside of the group's definition, and a collection could appear in more than one group. Click the title of a specific collection to search it alone. Sometimes it is advantageous to search a single collection. For example, search field and sorting options are often specific to the collection, allowing for a more refined search.

Some collections have a very narrow focus. Other collections are broader, and may encompass many sub-collections. Occassionally an image appears in multiple collections, though generally there is a single authoritative source for each image.
Select one or more databases to search. Click the database name to search it alone, often in more detail.

item.p: Matching words: The search engine attempts to match any word or phrase exactly as you put it in the box.
e.g.: Picasso and Rembrandt in a box will look for
Punctuation: All punctuation is treated as an empty space.
Case: The search engine is not case sensitive.
Wildcards: Use wildcard * to expand word stems. This is a good way to search for variations on a word.
Choose image collections: Limit your search to only those collections you choose in the image collections list.

Facets.Query: SELECT SQL_CALC_FOUND_ROWS b.field, b.value, COUNT(b.value) AS total FROM ItemBrowse b, ( SELECT istruct_isentryid FROM clark1ic8lift_media ) a WHERE b.field = ? AND b.collid = ? AND a.istruct_isentryid = b.idno GROUP BY b.field, b.value ORDER BY b.field, total DESC, b.value LIMIT 10

div.p: This collection contains images of maps from the Stephen S. Clark Library for Maps, Government Information and Data Services' map collection. The images in this collection are in the public domain but please attribute access and use of these digitized maps to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library. The print map collection from which these maps originate contains over 400,000 maps and is the principal collection for cartographic materials at the University of Michigan. We house the largest collection of printed maps in the state of Michigan, and one of the largest at an academic institution.

The University of Michigan Library provides access to these materials for educational and research purposes. These materials may be under copyright. If you decide to use any of these materials, you are responsible for making your own legal assessment and securing any necessary permission. If you have questions about the collection, please contact Clark Library for Maps Digital Collections Help. If you have concerns about the inclusion of an item in this collection, please contact Library Information Technology.
